cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of detecting and locating weapons in surveillance videos, which is a classic computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an ensemble of semantic Convolutional Neural Networks, which is a machine learning technique, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with security and surveillance, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper mentions simulations and real-world data, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
